      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/30/1/1/30",
      "text": [
        ": سمعت أبا عبد الله (ع) يقول المؤمنُ لا يمضي عليه أربعون ليلةً إلاّ عُرض له أمرٌ يحزِنه، ويُذكّره به."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.muhajir-b-ali": [
          "30. It has been narrated that Muhammad ibn Muslim said: I heard Abu 'Abd Allah (a.s) saying: No forty nights pass for a believer except a matter befalls him that grieves him and reminds him (of Allah)."
        ]
      }
